  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Takeda Nobuhiro no Super League Soccer (\"Nobuhiro Takeda's Super League Soccer\") is a soccer simulation video game licensed/endorsed by Takeda Nobuhiro, published by Jaleco Entertainment for the Super Famicom console, which was released exclusively in Japan in 1994.\n\nThis game is a sequel to Takeda Nobuhiro no Super Cup Soccer. It features club teams based on the top division of Japan Professional Football League J. League Division 1 (though unlicensed) instead of national teams. While it kept largely the same structure of the original game, some new options were added.",
